27/09/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia â Split Mayor Zeljko Kerum was elected on Friday (September 25th) a president of the new Croatian Civil Party (HGS). 
Kerum said the HGS aims to become a nationwide party and will set up branches in the major cities. 
It also aims to become the third biggest political party, after the ruling Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ) and the opposition Social Democratic Party (SDP). 
The HGS programme states the party will defend liberal and pro-European views. 
(24 Sata, HRT - 25/09/09)
